Ask HN: Reply.io Alternative with Strong API?
text:
I'm trying to create a cold email outreach sales funnel, but I want to keep the data in my own datawarehouse. I want to send emails and track whether the recipient has opened the email and clicked on the link.

I like Reply.io, but I cannot find an easy way to track campaign results per participants. I've looked into sending using Google Mail API, but tracking the open rate and click rate becomes a bit more cumbersome.

Any suggestions?

Show HN: Transmission Control, a new tool for Transmission BT client
text:
This is my new work I wrote in the last month. It was just released.

Overview A concise, lightweight and high-performance Transmission Manager and Web Extension. It supports managing multiple remote or local Transmission at the same time, as well as adding magnet links from BitTorrent websites.

Features Concise, lightweight and high-performance: Removed some not commonly used functions; The installation package size is small; Fast page loading, low CPU and memory usage. Support simultaneous management of download tasks in multiple remote Transmissions. Support adding download tasks by right-clicking on magnet links in Web pages. This extension doesn't require "Read and change all your data on all websites" permission.

Install Links: Chrome: https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/hfhhlbapamidaibjcg... Edge: https://microsoftedge.microsoft.com/addons/detail/pefbobclhi...
